A vintage 1960s-style technical illustration showing an intricate network of interconnected filing cabinets and card catalogs floating in space, with streams of paper documents and index cards flowing between them like ribbons. The cabinets have brass fixtures and warm wood tones, connected by ornate copper pipes and pneumatic tubes. Small mechanical gears and clockwork mechanisms are visible, suggesting automation. The color palette features muted teals, burnt oranges, and cream tones typical of mid-century technical manuals. The composition creates a sense of organized complexity, with documents transforming into structured grid patterns as they flow through the system.
